<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Novak Djokovic put past controversy aside to breeze past Sweden's Mikael Ymer in the first round of the French Open.</p>

<p>In his first Grand Slam match since being disqualified from the US Open after hitting a ball at a line judge, Djokovic won in straight sets. </p>

<p>His victory came in just an hour and 38 minutes, with the Serbian looking for yet another Grand Slam title. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

<p>Novak Djokovic is through to the next round of the French Open after a straight sets victory</p>

<p>He defeated Sweden's Mikael Ymer 6-0, 6-2, 6-3 on his return to Grand Slam action</p>

<p>Djokovic was appearing in his first Grand Slam since being disqualified from the US Open</p>

<p>The Serbian didn't lose a game in the first set, and powered to a win in just over 98 minutes</p>
